<h2>JavaScript getDay()</h2>
<p>The getDay() method returns the weekday as a number:</p>
<p>You can use an array to dispal the name of the weekday:</p>

<p id="demo"></p>

<script>
cnst d = new Date();
const days =
["Sunday","Monday","Tuesday","Wednesday","Thursday","Friday","Sartuday"];
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = days[d.getDay()];
</script>

